<span key="57f5c56df6b84337817fb073a8f5a42c"><span offset-key="57f5c56df6b84337817fb073a8f5a42c:0">Steps for Pull Request </span></span>

1.  <span class="r-1awozwy r-1nf4jbm r-6koalj r-18u37iz r-gg6oyi r-ubezar r-16dba41 r-135wba7 r-1m04atk r-1pyaxff" contenteditable="false" style="height:24px">1.</span>
    <span key="b05c18d3360a40fc969d7f6e2c59ec0b"><span offset-key="b05c18d3360a40fc969d7f6e2c59ec0b:0">Git Status - to see what files were updated</span></span>

2.  <span class="r-1awozwy r-1nf4jbm r-6koalj r-18u37iz r-gg6oyi r-ubezar r-16dba41 r-135wba7 r-1m04atk r-1pyaxff" contenteditable="false" style="height:24px">2.</span>

    <span key="da4ed138aea14aafa9864f051f685648"><span offset-key="da4ed138aea14aafa9864f051f685648:0">My changes generate no new warnings</span></span>

-   <img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," class="r-1nf4jbm" />

    <span key="a9e4cef4010f4a68a0697a8d97aab41c"><span offset-key="a9e4cef4010f4a68a0697a8d97aab41c:0">There are no merge conflicts</span></span>

# 

<span key="bfa94200e5e44f86a4c592abf2b6af0d"><span offset-key="bfa94200e5e44f86a4c592abf2b6af0d:0">GitHub Basics</span></span>

## 

<span key="e8ae468cb17143beb115e89bf849be2c"><span offset-key="e8ae468cb17143beb115e89bf849be2c:0">The Labs GitHub Org</span></span>

<span key="5b6dcc859f804e93b386fa2c7a213a3a"><span offset-key="5b6dcc859f804e93b386fa2c7a213a3a:0">Lambda Labs maintains a GitHub organization (</span></span><a href="https://github.com/Lambda-School-Labs" class="css-4rbku5 css-1dbjc4n r-1loqt21 r-1471scf r-1otgn73 r-1i6wzkk r-lrvibr"><span data-key="14edc0dcc8854749bd9f78e9d1d4a12d" data-rnw-int-class="nearest_257-53494_259-53495-237__"><span data-key="0cd3e207dec54a01b3f49a9e924fcd1f"><span data-offset-key="0cd3e207dec54a01b3f49a9e924fcd1f:0">https://github.com/Lambda-School-Labs</span></span></span></a><span key="b4e389e6499249688797d1e8802f802f"><span offset-key="b4e389e6499249688797d1e8802f802f:0">) which houses all of the Labs projects (with few exceptions) that are built by student teams during Labs.</span></span>

### 

<span key="c5c031cd7e404ba5931693ad1556315c"><span offset-key="c5c031cd7e404ba5931693ad1556315c:0">The Basics</span></span>

-   <img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," class="r-1nf4jbm" />

    <span key="736c5d0ca39449ed89e9ed4355de08d5"><span offset-key="736c5d0ca39449ed89e9ed4355de08d5:0">All repositories are </span></span><a href="https://help.github.com/en/github/administering-a-repository/setting-repository-visibility" class="css-4rbku5 css-1dbjc4n r-1loqt21 r-1471scf r-1otgn73 r-1i6wzkk r-lrvibr"><span data-key="8317610d187049c0af217b7e758ec686" data-rnw-int-class="nearest_257-53494_259-53495-237__"><span data-key="92c2fa4a0a624e3abb87f47f8ccd43af"><span data-offset-key="92c2fa4a0a624e3abb87f47f8ccd43af:0">publicly accessible</span></span></span></a><span key="e2dcb31408a740a3be9fffa8b52481d0"><span offset-key="e2dcb31408a740a3be9fffa8b52481d0:0"> and licensed under </span></span><a href="https://opensource.org/licenses/MIT" class="css-4rbku5 css-1dbjc4n r-1loqt21 r-1471scf r-1otgn73 r-1i6wzkk r-lrvibr"><span data-key="499f359c5c7d47c2bfc0ea0703977ca2" data-rnw-int-class="nearest_257-53494_259-53495-237__"><span data-key="38a83a1f7685405d8da6e841d94d5812"><span data-offset-key="38a83a1f7685405d8da6e841d94d5812:0">The MIT License</span></span></span></a><span key="fb9ad62dfea3409aa1201e5952ffe211"><span offset-key="fb9ad62dfea3409aa1201e5952ffe211:0"><span slate-zero-width="z">​</span></span></span>

    -   <img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," class="r-1nf4jbm" />

        <span key="8c65459f8ff04e438c18072bc9aba096"><span offset-key="8c65459f8ff04e438c18072bc9aba096:0">This effectively means that the code in the repositories belongs to the world; Lambda School simply maintains the organization to keep the code accessible and organized.</span></span>

-   <img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," class="r-1nf4jbm" />

    <span key="a3dfe2dffe3942928fc167cd08f8aa5c"><span offset-key="a3dfe2dffe3942928fc167cd08f8aa5c:0">Only Lambda School Engineering Managers will have the role of Owner in the organization, everyone else will have the role of Member</span></span>

    -   <img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," class="r-1nf4jbm" />

        <span key="72078052b297482c8991ec9d9df37f16"><span offset-key="72078052b297482c8991ec9d9df37f16:0">The Member role has very limited permissions and will only be able to access repositories that are specifically assigned to the user, directly or through Teams. Work with an Engineering Manager for any administrative tasks</span></span>

### 

<span key="0141e456a91a4b2a9d7b75ada65dc252"><span offset-key="0141e456a91a4b2a9d7b75ada65dc252:0">GitHub Teams</span></span>

<span key="17d2f23ad3bf4054bd6d8abff6b17d44"><span offset-key="17d2f23ad3bf4054bd6d8abff6b17d44:0">Member permissions for teams are generally granted using </span></span><a href="https://help.github.com/en/github/setting-up-and-managing-organizations-and-teams/organizing-members-into-teams" class="css-4rbku5 css-1dbjc4n r-1loqt21 r-1471scf r-1otgn73 r-1i6wzkk r-lrvibr"><span data-key="4f8c48d33a9b448b91d373749c1a8d65" data-rnw-int-class="nearest_257-53494_259-53495-237__"><span data-key="c970d28344624d37b73bda21f8d32d0a"><span data-offset-key="c970d28344624d37b73bda21f8d32d0a:0">Teams</span></span></span></a><span key="3bb884f6def64eb8825302f018c8d77a"><span offset-key="3bb884f6def64eb8825302f018c8d77a:0">. This allows individual member permissions to be more easily maintained and made consistent. A GitHub team will be created for each Labs team with a specific naming convention to identify the team: </span>`<Cohort>-<Team Letter>-<Product Name>`<span offset-key="3bb884f6def64eb8825302f018c8d77a:2"> (e.g. </span>`Labs 26 - A - Apollo`<span offset-key="3bb884f6def64eb8825302f018c8d77a:4">).</span></span>

-   <img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," class="r-1nf4jbm" />

    <span key="0a3af2210c4047b4976c473dadb1f06e"><span offset-key="0a3af2210c4047b4976c473dadb1f06e:0">There will be one team per project, per cohort.</span></span>

-   <img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," class="r-1nf4jbm" />

    <span key="14ca0ade0604439e89bcba3fa34a2b86"><span offset-key="14ca0ade0604439e89bcba3fa34a2b86:0">The APL, TPL and all students that are part of the project will be members of this team.</span></span>

-   <img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," class="r-1nf4jbm" />

    <span key="e4962ee14f014f9cb6357a1ce0a1cad2"><span offset-key="e4962ee14f014f9cb6357a1ce0a1cad2:0">Teams will be deleted shortly after the Labs cohort ends.</span></span>

    -   <img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," class="r-1nf4jbm" />

        <span key="2ebaafb5d3a24b259db060045b00b44e"><span offset-key="2ebaafb5d3a24b259db060045b00b44e:0">This means Team members will lose direct access to the code in the Labs org... but don't worry! The code is public and MIT licensed, so you can fork away to continue working on the code!</span></span>

<span key="6003b0d8683448c2b42f7888f044123a"><span offset-key="6003b0d8683448c2b42f7888f044123a:0">To be a member of a Team, you must be a member of the Organization that the Team is part of. If this is your first time on a Labs team, Labby will invite you to be a member of the Labs GitHub Organization. This invite </span>*should*<span offset-key="6003b0d8683448c2b42f7888f044123a:2"> arrive in the email that is associated with your GitHub account. If it doesn't, check your spam filter folder. If it's not there, you </span>*should*<span offset-key="6003b0d8683448c2b42f7888f044123a:4"> be able to see the invite in your GitHub notifications tab: </span></span><a href="https://github.com/notifications" class="css-4rbku5 css-1dbjc4n r-1loqt21 r-1471scf r-1otgn73 r-1i6wzkk r-lrvibr"><span data-key="9ef7738218534c1a9a65b1e5c76f8af6" data-rnw-int-class="nearest_257-53494_259-53495-237__"><span data-key="bec16e3e6f444b609dba40bf245a353c"><span data-offset-key="bec16e3e6f444b609dba40bf245a353c:0">https://github.com/notifications</span></span></span></a><span key="55126d07b33947f0a871a94e636cb975"><span offset-key="55126d07b33947f0a871a94e636cb975:0"><span slate-zero-width="z">​</span></span></span>

<span key="a89f43eda3a04ae9b4f7f8371694e5b8"><span offset-key="a89f43eda3a04ae9b4f7f8371694e5b8:0">If you think you should have an invite, but can't find it, please talk to a Section Lead or Tech Lead.</span></span>

### 

<span key="5735abf1660845cf8c533a780b299ad8"><span offset-key="5735abf1660845cf8c533a780b299ad8:0">Why am I being automatically subscribed to new repositories?</span></span>

<span key="8ebb1ae23124412c8cc97fc56f64c2f1"><span offset-key="8ebb1ae23124412c8cc97fc56f64c2f1:0">Automatic subscriptions are controlled via your personal settings: </span></span><a href="https://github.com/settings/notifications" class="css-4rbku5 css-1dbjc4n r-1loqt21 r-1471scf r-1otgn73 r-1i6wzkk r-lrvibr"><span data-key="b84b8b108b86474ba2bfcedfd6519e75" data-rnw-int-class="nearest_257-53494_259-53495-237__"><span data-key="7c8f04716b1c4e0cb08511fee64a3580"><span data-offset-key="7c8f04716b1c4e0cb08511fee64a3580:0">https://github.com/settings/notifications</span></span></span></a><span key="3f7e15e2d8cd4bb4872d1a8ba99d4a1d"><span offset-key="3f7e15e2d8cd4bb4872d1a8ba99d4a1d:0"><span slate-zero-width="z">​</span></span></span>
